  "body": "(Followup to #2777)\r\n\r\nOSDs are now bootstrapped with `ceph-volume`, with optional metadataDevice.   `ceph-volume` does all the magic putting db volume onto metadataDevice, if it is a faster device (eg ssd).  If one specify hdd for both metadataDevice, and device, `ceph-volume` will actually create two hdd OSDs, which is not what the user would expected.  In this case, the metadataDevice config should be rejected. it should warn the user, and proceed with bootstrapping the osd without metadataDevice.",
